The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 20 August is 278,551 (494.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 August, there were 6,782 new confirmed cases (12.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 August, there were 5,764 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 18% (1018 extra cases).
